ckheed%20Martin's%20new%20hypersonic%20missile%20can%20be%20fired%20from%20most%20US%20fighter%20jets%2C%20including%20the%20F-22.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20can%20engage%20air-%20and%20sea-based%20targets%20within%20enemy%20defenses%20or%20at%20longer%20ranges%20at%20Mach%205%20speeds.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUS%20Navy%20warships%20could%20also%20potentially%20deploy%20the%20Mako%20if%20equipped%20with%20a%20booster.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Martin%20has%20released%20new%20details%20about%20the%20air-launched%20hypersonic%20Mako%20missile%2C%20which%20promises%20to%20be%20the%20first%20hypersonic%20weapon%20in%20the%20world%20that%20can%20be%20launched%20from%20the%20internal%20weapons%20bay%20of%20not%20just%20the%20F-35%2C%20but%20the%20F-22%20Raptor%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20missile%20has%20been%20under%20development%20for%20seven%20years%20and%20has%20been%20touted%20by%20Lockheed%20officials%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmulti-mission%26quot%3B%20weapon%20system%20capable%20of%20maritime%20strike%2C%20counter-air%20defense%2C%20and%20a%20variety%20of%20other%20surface-attack%20operations.%20It%20was%20originally%20developed%20for%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%2C%20but%20now%20may%20find%20a%20home%20with%20the%20US%20Navy%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHypersonic%20missiles%20are%20weapons%20that%20are%20capable%20of%20achieving%20sustained%20speeds%20in%20excess%20of%20Mach%205%20while%20maneuvering.%20But%20while%20speed%20may%20draw%20most%20of%20the%20headlines%2C%20it's%20the%20combination%20of%20velocity%20and%20unpredictable%20course%20changes%20that%20make%20these%20weapons%20so%20difficult%20to%20intercept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMako%20does%20not%20travel%20in%20a%20pure%20arcing%20ballistic%20flight%20path.%20It%20is%20a%20true%20hypersonic%20weapon%20that%20operates%20and%20maneuvers%20in%20a%20high-altitude%20hypersonic%20regime%2C%26quot%3B%20Paul%20Sudlow%20from%20Lockheed%20Martin%20Missiles%20and%20Fire%20Control%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fmako-arming-the-f-35-with-hypersonic-missiles%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20Sandboxx%20News.%20%26quot%3BIts%20high%20speed%20and%20maneuverability%20enable%20it%20to%20penetrate%20advanced%20air-defense%20systems%2C%20engaging%20targets%20at%20or%20below%20hypersonic%20speeds%2C%20depending%20on%20mission%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f9988c9-cca9-4983-80c9-fce60b47f052%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EAdding%20the%20Mako%20missile%20to%20America's%20stealth%20fighters%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22990%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20render%20of%20an%20F-35%20equipped%20with%20Mako%20missiles.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3c812a0fc5856d597bfc6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22556%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20render%20of%20an%20F-35%20equipped%20with%20Mako%20missiles.%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Martin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20Mako%20missile%20was%20developed%20under%20the%20auspices%20of%20the%20Air%20Force's%20Stand-In%20Attack%20Weapon%20program.%20A%20total%20of%20some%20%2435%20million%20was%20awarded%20to%20Lockheed%20Martin%20in%20three%20separate%20developmental%20contracts%20(associated%20with%20developmental%20phases%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbreakingdefense.com%2F2023%2F03%2Fair-force-program-for-new-f-35a-missile-will-knock-out-at-least-one-prime-in-fy24%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1.1%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defensedaily.com%2Fusaf-awards-contracts-for-next-phase-of-stand-in-attack-weapon-to-lockheed-martin-nothrop-grumman-and-l3harris%2Fair-force%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1.2%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedefensepost.com%2F2023%2F03%2F02%2Fus-af-stand-in-attack-weapon%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUS%2520Air%2520Force%2520Awards%2520Stand%252DIn%2520Attack%2520Weapon%2520Phase%25201.3%2520Contracts%2C-Inder%2520Singh%2520Bisht%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520US%2520Air%2520Force%2520has%2Ccompleted%2520by%2520August%252026%252C%25202023.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1.3%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20aim%20was%20to%20field%20a%20weapon%20that%20could%20effectively%20engage%20China's%20anti-access%2Farea%20denial%20assets%20in%20the%20Pacific%20%E2%80%94%20so%20the%20weapon%20has%20to%20be%20quick%2C%20powerful%2C%20and%20survivable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHypersonic%20missiles%20are%20traditionally%20too%20large%20to%20fit%20inside%20the%20internal%20weapons%20bays%20of%20stealth%20fighters.%20This%20is%20because%20they%20usually%20require%20a%20large%20rocket%20motor%20and%20sufficient%20fuel%20stores%20to%20carry%20them%20to%20high%20speeds%20and%20altitudes.%20They%20then%20separate%20from%20the%20booster%20and%20continue%20on%20unpowered%20or%20under%20an%20alternate%20form%20of%20propulsion%20(as%20is%20the%20case%20with%20the%20Air%20Force's%20scramjet-powered%20Hypersonic%20Attack%20Cruise%20Missile).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Mako%20missile's%20ability%20to%20be%20launched%20from%20within%20America's%20stealth%20fighters%20dramatically%20increases%20the%20potential%20vectors%20the%20weapon%20can%20attack%20from%2C%20substantially%20complicating%20matters%20for%20air%20defenses%20tasked%20with%20identifying%20and%20intercepting%20inbound%20threats.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntercepting%20a%20maneuvering%20Mach%205%2B%20weapon%20launched%20from%20a%20fighter%20or%20bomber%20you%20can%20see%20on%20radar%20might%20be%20an%20extremely%20difficult%20proposition%20today%20for%20even%20the%20most%20advanced%20air%20defense%20systems%2C%20but%20intercepting%20one%20from%20seemingly%20anywhere%20would%20be%20even%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Sudlow%20told%20Sandboxx%20News%20today%2C%20this%20high-speed%20weapon%20is%20also%20designed%20to%20allow%20for%20stealth%20aircraft%2C%20like%20America's%205th-generation%20fighters%2C%20to%20fly%20out%20ahead%2C%20locate%20a%20target%2C%20and%20then%20relay%20that%20target%20data%20back%20to%20Mako-armed%204th-generation%20fighters%20carrying%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20Sniper%20Networked%20Targeting%20Pod%20for%20engagement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FQNfwNsa55ys%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Introducing%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20Mako%E2%84%A2%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20allow%20older%204th-generation%20platforms%20to%20play%20a%20vital%20role%20in%20combat%20operations%2C%20even%20against%20targets%20in%20highly%20contested%20airspace%2C%20and%20further%20increase%20the%20destructive%20capabilities%20of%205th-generation%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20this%20end%2C%20Sudlow%20also%20confirmed%20that%20the%20Mako%20missile%20has%20already%20been%20fit-checked%20to%20be%20carried%20externally%20by%20the%20F%2FA-18%20Super%20Hornet%2C%20EA-18G%20Growler%2C%20F-15E%20Strike%20Eagle%2C%20F-16C%20Fighting%20Falcon%2C%20and%20even%20the%20P-8A%20Poseidon.%20In%20effect%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin%20designed%20this%20weapon%20to%20be%20carried%20by%20nearly%20any%20aircraft%20in%20the%20US%20arsenal%20carrying%20fairly%20standard%2030-inch%20lugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20the%20Mako%20missile%20could%20be%20another%20new%20long-range%20weapon%20in%20the%20Navy's%20arsenal%2C%20alongside%20its%20recently%20revealed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fthe-us-navys-insane-new-air-to-air-missile-the-aim-174%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAIM-174B%20air-to-air%20missile%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Both%20Mako%20and%20the%20AIM-174B%20are%20believed%20to%20offer%20ranges%20well%20into%20the%20hundreds%20of%20miles%2C%20meaning%20these%20two%20weapons%20could%20provide%20a%20significant%20long-range%20one-two%20punch%20against%20air-%20and%20sea-based%20targets.%20Lockheed%20Martin%20even%20says%20the%20Mako%20missile%20could%20be%20fired%20from%20the%20vertical%20launch%20tubes%20on%20the%20Navy's%20warships%20if%20equipped%20with%20a%20booster%2C%20similar%20to%20what's%20been%20done%20with%20the%20AGM-158C%20LRASM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20this%20weapon%20could%20find%20its%20way%20back%20to%20the%20Air%20Force%20%E2%80%94%20assuming%20the%20Navy%20opts%20to%20put%20Mako%20into%20production.%20This%20could%20see%20it%20carried%20by%204th-generation%20fighters%20supporting%20forward%20F-22%20or%20F-35%20operations%2C%20or%20even%20see%20it%20carried%20internally%20by%20the%20F-22%20Raptor%20itself%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20still%20the%20stealthiest%20fighter%20ever%20to%20reach%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weapon%20can%20also%20be%20carried%20internally%20by%20the%20Air%20Force's%20F-35As%20and%20Navy%20and%20Marine%20Corps%20F-35Cs.%20The%20only%20American%20stealth%20aircraft%20that%20can't%20fit%20this%20new%20missile%20is%20the%20vertical%20landing%20F-35B%2C%20as%20its%20internal%20storage%20capacity%20is%20limited%20by%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20aircraft's%20lifting%20fan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2246a3f4cd-a553-461a-8e10-74b4b6fc599a%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENamed%20after%20the%20fastest%20shark%20in%20the%20sea%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Shortfin%20Mako%20Shark%20swims%20just%20under%20the%20surface%2C%20breaking%20the%20water%20with%20its%20dorsal%20fin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3cad5a0fc5856d597c1d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Shortfin%20Mako%20Shark%20swims%20just%20under%20the%20surface%2C%20breaking%20the%20water%20with%20its%20dorsal%20fin.%3Cp%3ENano%20Calvo%2FVWPics%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMako%20was%20originally%20developed%20as%20a%20part%20of%20the%20US%20Air%20Force's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Famericas-new-precision-strike-missile-has-china-in-its-crosshairs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStand-In%20Attack%20Weapon%3C%2Fa%3E%20(SiAW)%20program.%20That%20effort%20aimed%20to%20field%20an%20air-launched%20weapon%20meant%20specifically%20to%20counter%20elements%20of%20anti-access%20area%20denial%20defenses%20like%20air%20defense%20radar%20platforms%2C%20surface-to-air%20missile%20systems%2C%20and%20anti-ship%20missile%20launchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThat%20contract%20ultimately%20went%20to%20Northrop%20Grumman%20for%20a%20new%20missile%20system%20derived%20from%20its%20radar-hunting%20AGM-88G%20Advanced%20Anti-Radiation%20Guided%20Missile-Extended%20Range%20(AARGM-ER).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Lockheed%20Martin%20recognized%20that%20its%20entry%20to%20the%20competition%20could%20have%20much%20further%20reaching%20implications%20than%20the%20suppression%20of%20enemy%20air%20defenses%20alone.%20As%20such%2C%20the%20company%20is%20pitching%20this%20new%20missile%20design%20to%20the%20Navy%20as%20a%20multi-purpose%20air-to-surface%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20US%20Navy%2C%20this%20is%20a%20multi-mission%2C%20highly%20capable%20system%2C%20highly%20survivable%2C%20affordable%2C%20so%20you're%20going%20to%20hold%20many%20targets%20at%20risk%20with%20one%20weapons%20system%20that's%20ready%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Rick%20Loy%2C%20Senior%20Program%20Manager%20at%20the%20company's%20Missile%20and%20Fire%20Control%20division%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navalnews.com%2Fevent-news%2Fsea-air-space-2024%2F2024%2F04%2Flockheed-martin-unveils-mako-hypersonic-missile%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENaval%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20name%2C%20Mako%2C%20is%20derived%20from%20the%20world's%20fastest%20shark%2C%20the%20Shortfin%20Mako%2C%20which%20is%20capable%20of%20swimming%20as%20fast%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foceana.org%2Fmarine-life%2Fshortfin-mako-shark%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWith%2520top%2520speeds%2520of%252045%2Crestricted%2520to%2520its%2520swimming%2520speeds.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E45%20miles%20per%20hour%3C%2Fa%3E%20(74%20kilometers%20per%20hour).%20It's%20a%20fitting%20name%20for%20a%20weapon%20that's%20capable%20of%20screaming%20across%20the%20sky%20at%20better%20than%203%2C836%20miles%20per%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2013%20feet%2C%20the%20missile%20is%2C%20appropriately%20enough%2C%20about%20as%20long%20as%20a%20Mako%20shark%20might%20grow.%20At%201%2C300%20pounds%20and%20about%2013%20inches%20in%20diameter%2C%20this%20broadly%20capable%20missile%20is%20only%20about%20an%20inch%20longer%20than%20the%20AIM-120%20AMRAAM%20that%20America's%20stealth%20fighters%20were%20designed%20to%20carry%3B%20though%20Mako%20comes%20with%20significantly%20more%20heft%2C%20at%20nearly%20twice%20the%20AMRAAM's%20diameter%20and%20more%20than%20three%20times%20the%20weight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2217ae7828-b6bb-4703-8a08-2423b017c7e4%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDesigned%20in%20a%20'digital%20engineering%20ecosystem'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20render%20shows%20the%20Mako%20hypersonic%20missile%20in%20flight.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3c8a2aab37011780ada0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20render%20shows%20the%20Mako%20hypersonic%20missile%20in%20flight.%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Martin%20Europe%2FX%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThis%20new%20Mach%205%2B%20missile%20was%20among%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20first%20to%20be%20designed%20from%20the%20ground%20up%20entirely%20within%20a%20digital%20environment%2C%20which%20is%20in%20keeping%20with%20broader%20Pentagon%20efforts%20to%20use%20digital%20design%20and%20testing%20to%20reduce%20the%20real-world%20costs%20associated%20with%20testing%20and%20design%20revisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBy%20designing%20and%20then%20testing%20the%20weapon%20in%20the%20digital%20world%20first%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin%20can%20produce%20a%20much%20more%20mature%20design%20at%20the%20onset%20of%20operational%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20despite%20the%20high%20level%20of%20capability%20promised%20by%20this%20new%20weapon%2C%20Lockheed%20went%20out%20of%20its%20way%20not%20to%20invent%20any%20unnecessary%20components.%20Instead%2C%20when%20possible%2C%20it%20pulled%20from%20several%20already-fielded%20systems%20with%20existing%20and%20proven%20supply%20chains%20to%20reduce%20the%20number%20of%20variables%20that%20could%20potentially%20affect%20a%20production%20order.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Lockheed%20Martin's%20press%20materials%20point%20out%2C%20the%20firm%20also%20brought%20manufacturing%20engineers%20in%20at%20the%20earliest%20stages%20of%20development%20to%20help%20streamline%20the%20sometimes%20messy%20transition%20from%20advanced%20prototyping%20to%20serialized%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22990%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20close-up%20of%20the%20Mako's%20guidance%20section%20under%20inspection.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3ca1ea0fc5856d597c173%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22771%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20close-up%20of%20the%20Mako's%20guidance%20section%20under%20inspection.%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Martin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Martin%20has%20not%20been%20specific%20about%20the%20guidance%20system%20carried%20inside%20the%20Mako%2C%20but%20that%20could%20be%20by%20design.%20The%20weapon's%20original%20intended%20mission%20set%20for%20the%20Stand-in%20Attack%20Role%20suggested%20the%20use%20of%20a%20multi-mode%20seeker%20that%20would%20likely%20include%20anti-radiation%20(radar-hunting)%20capabilities%20alongside%20GPS%2Finertial%20guidance%20and%20potentially%20a%20millimeter-wave%20radar%20seeker%20to%20boot%2C%20allowing%20the%20weapon%20to%20close%20with%20just%20about%20any%20target%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20earth%20whether%20moving%20or%20stationary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20as%20Lockheed%20Martin%20has%20pointed%20out%20in%20promotional%20materials%2C%20the%20Mako%20was%20specifically%20designed%20with%20modularity%20in%20mind%2C%20allowing%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Brapid%20integration%20of%20mission-specific%20elements%20like%20warheads%20and%20seekers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20Lockheed%20specified%20that%20this%20modular%20design%20fully%20embraces%20the%20concept%20of%20open%20system%20architecture%2C%20meaning%20the%20Pentagon%20would%20not%20be%20beholden%20to%20the%20firm%20for%20future%20upgrades%20or%20updates.%20This%20is%20in%20keeping%20with%20force-wide%20Pentagon%20initiatives%20to%20field%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20weapon%20systems%20and%20platforms%20that%20are%20easier%20(and%20cheaper)%20to%20upgrade%20over%20decade-spanning%20service%20lives%20that%20are%20common%20for%20many%20of%20today's%20military%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283f42dcc-d83f-4f57-ac48-ab297cdeab35%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20hypersonics%20affordable%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Visitors%20observe%20missiles%20from%20Lockheed%20Martin%20on%20display%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3c9ea1a227600e631f950%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVisitors%20observe%20missiles%20from%20Lockheed%20Martin%20on%20display%20during%20a%20defense%20fair%20in%20London.%3Cp%3ELeon%20Neal%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20facing%20the%20laundry%20list%20of%20hypersonic%20weapons%20in%20active%20development%20for%20the%20US%20military%20is%20cost.%20In%202021%2C%20the%20Defense%20Department%20projected%20that%20some%20of%20America's%20hypersonic%20missiles%20may%20cost%20as%20much%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2021-11-12%2Fhypersonic-sticker-shock-u-s-weapons-may-run-106-million-each%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24106%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20weapon%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20the%20purchase%20price%20of%20a%20brand-new%20F-35%20%E2%80%94%20leading%20many%20to%20argue%20that%20these%20missiles%20simply%20aren't%20economically%20viable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20significant%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20the%20overall%20cost%20of%20these%20weapon%20systems%20have%20been%20underway%20for%20some%20time%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airandspaceforces.com%2Fcbo-estimates-15-18-million-cost-per-arrw-hypersonic-missile%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20recent%3C%2Fa%3E%20assessments%20out%20of%20the%20Congressional%20Budget%20Office%20now%20projecting%20the%20per-unit%20cost%20of%20another%20Lockheed%20Martin-sourced%20hypersonic%20missile%2C%20the%20AGM-183%20ARRW%2C%20at%20roughly%20%2415-%2418%20million%20a%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Mako%20continues%20this%20pursuit%20of%20cost%20savings%20by%20leaning%20into%20new%20additive%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%94%20or%203D%20printing%20%E2%80%94%20technologies.%20The%20Mako%20missile's%20guidance%20section%20and%20fins%20are%20all%20produced%20through%20this%20additive%20manufacturing%20process%2C%20which%20Lockheed%20claims%20is%20ten%20times%20faster%20than%20traditional%20production%20methods%20while%20coming%20in%20at%20just%201%2F10%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Martin%20has%20not%20disclosed%20the%20price%20point%20for%20this%20weapon%2C%20but%20it%20would%20certainly%20be%20predicated%20on%20projected%20order%20size%2C%20which%20would%20be%20impossible%20to%20assume%20at%20this%20point%2C%20with%20no%20contract%20yet%20in%20place%20for%20any%20branch%20to%20purchase%20this%20new%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20MORE%20FROM%20SANDBOXX%20NEWS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fnavy-wants-to-add-decoys-to-its-f-35s-in-preparation-for-a-near-peer-conflict%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENavy%20wants%20to%20add%20decoys%20to%20its%20F-35s%20in%20preparation%20for%20a%20near-peer%20conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fsocom-and-marines-will-get-new-machine-gun-that-breaks-the-mold-to-replace-old-classic%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESOCOM%20and%20Marines%20will%20get%20new%20machine%20gun%20that%20breaks%20the%20mold%20to%20replace%20old%20classic%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sandboxx.us%2Fnews%2Fvideo-the-wild-story-behind-americas-rocket-powered-c-130s%2F%5C%22%20target%