epsiCo%20is%20using%20robotics%20and%20AI-powered%20crop%20planning%20to%20transform%20its%20supply%20chain%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Boxes%20of%20Pepsi%20soda%20are%20seen%20on%20display%20at%20a%20Target%20store%20on%20February%2009%2C%202024%20in%20the%20Flatbush%20neighborhood%20of%20Brooklyn%20borough%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ca0103610ab33aa5deed91%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20M.%20Santiago%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPepsiCo%20says%20it's%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20way%20done%20with%20an%20overhaul%20of%20its%20supply%20chain.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20has%20invested%20in%20AI%20and%20automation%20to%20make%20its%20production%20and%20distribution%20more%20profitable.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20article%20is%20part%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fthe-future-of-supply-chain-management%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Future%20of%20Supply-Chain%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20series%20on%20companies'%20manufacturing%20and%20distribution%20strategies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EGregg%20Roden%2C%20PepsiCo's%20chief%20operating%20officer%2C%20has%20spent%20his%20entire%2034-year%20professional%20career%20working%20at%20the%20snacking%20giant.%20He%20said%20that%20in%20the%20past%20three%20years%20alone%20he'd%20witnessed%20more%20change%20than%20in%20the%2031%20years%20before%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20decades%2C%20as%20consumers%20bought%20more%20goods%20online%2C%20grocery%20sales%20remained%20reliably%20stuck%20in%20the%20store.%20But%20the%20pandemic%20shifted%20grocery-shopping%20patterns%2C%20and%20now%20people%20are%20increasingly%20likely%20to%20buy%20food%20and%20beverages%20online%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20started%2034%20years%20ago%2C%20everything%20was%20bought%20from%20a%20store%2C%20and%20we%20had%20a%20pretty%20narrow%20portfolio%20of%20options%20for%20the%20consumer%2C%26quot%3B%20Roden%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20literally%20anyone%20can%20buy%20anything%2C%20anywhere.%26quot%3B%20PepsiCo%20has%20also%20expanded%20its%20product%20line%2C%20offering%20new%20flavors%20and%20sizes%20of%20its%20snacks%20and%20drinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20changes%20mean%20demand%20for%20more%20brands%20is%20coming%20from%20more%20directions.%20PepsiCo%20says%20it%20is%20investing%20in%20digitization%20and%20automation%20%E2%80%94%20including%20robotics%20and%20predictive%20artificial%20intelligence%20%E2%80%94%20so%20it%20can%20better%20plan%20for%20demand%20and%20more%20quickly%20and%20precisely%20produce%20and%20deliver%20its%20products.%20And%20it%20says%20its%20supply-chain%20transformation%20is%20two-thirds%20complete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22edb5b524-83f3-4f66-928d-fc4bdede46a4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupporting%20agriculture%20with%20AI%20predictive%20insights%20and%20satellite%20imagery%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPepsiCo%20generated%20more%20than%20%2491%20billion%20in%202023%20from%20the%20sales%20of%20more%20than%20500%20brands%20worldwide%2C%20including%20its%20namesake%20soda%2C%20Lay's%2C%20Doritos%2C%20Gatorade%2C%20and%20Mountain%20Dew.%20The%20company's%20earnings%20for%20the%20first%20two%20quarters%20of%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2024%2F07%2F11%2Fpepsico-pep-earnings-q2-2024-earnings.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexceeded%20Wall%20Street's%20expectations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20volume%20in%20North%20America%20for%20the%20Frito-Lay%20and%20beverages%20businesses%20has%20been%20declining%20as%20consumers%20have%20pushed%20back%20against%20years%20of%20price%20hikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAthina%20Kanioura%2C%20PepsiCo's%20chief%20strategy%20and%20transformation%20officer%2C%20described%20investments%20in%20PepsiCo's%20seed-to-shelf%20supply%20chain%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bglue%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20company's%20future%20ability%20to%20deliver%20higher%20profits%20and%20revenue%20growth.%20And%20it%20all%20begins%20with%20the%20work%20done%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20farmers%20PepsiCo%20works%20with%20own%20more%20than%204%20million%20acres%20in%20North%20America%20alone%2C%20providing%20ingredients%20such%20as%20potatoes%20and%20corn%20for%20its%20chips%20and%20other%20snacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thinking%20is%20that%20by%20using%20less%20water%20and%20fertilizer%20to%20produce%20those%20ingredients%2C%20the%20company%20can%20boost%20its%20profits%20in%20an%20industry%20that%20operates%20on%20thin%20margins.%20It%20says%20that%20it%20works%20with%20farmers%20to%20ensure%20they%20have%20the%20technology%20to%20harvest%20those%20ingredients%20efficiently%20and%20that%20it%20subsidizes%20some%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20that%20technology%20for%20smaller%20farms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20says%20it%20has%20partnered%20with%20companies%20including%20CropTrak%2C%20AgroScout%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20to%20monitor%20production%2C%20analyze%20crop%20health%2C%20track%20where%20crops%20go%2C%20and%20better%20understand%20where%20to%20plant%20crops%20so%20they%20can%20thrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2232588e1b-3851-4dba-89dd-e96f1f24974a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDistribution%20workers%20do%20fewer%20manual%20tasks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPepsiCo%20is%20also%20rethinking%20how%20it%20fulfills%20orders%20and%20distributes%20its%20products%2C%20which%20is%20changing%20the%20work%20of%20the%20company's%20many%20employees%20in%20manufacturing%20and%20distribution.%20With%20more%20automation%2C%20workers%20are%20doing%20fewer%20physical%20tasks%2C%20like%20driving%20a%20forklift%2C%20and%20far%20more%20oversight%20of%20the%20machines%20taking%20over%20those%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20at%20manufacturing%20facilities%20and%20distribution%20centers%20and%20the%20unions%20that%20represent%20them%20often%20bristle%20at%20automation%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20layoffs.%20Large%20food%20manufacturers%20that%20have%20announced%20closings%20and%20layoffs%20this%20year%20include%20PepsiCo%2C%20Tyson%20Foods%2C%20and%20Campbell%20Soup.%20Often%20those%20announcing%20layoffs%20don't%20directly%20attribute%20them%20to%20automation%20but%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fcommodities%2Ftyson-foods-close-iowa-pork-plant-with-1200-workers-2024-03-11%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoft%20sales%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fooddive.com%2Fnews%2Fcampbell-soup-closing-inefficient-sites-415-job-losses%2F717224%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eolder%20facilities%20that%20can't%20keep%20up%20with%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fooddive.com%2Fnews%2Fpepsicos-quaker-plant-illinois-closing-layoffs%2F712954%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeven%20product%20recalls%3C%2Fa%3E.%20PepsiCo%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20reason%20for%20its%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFood%20producers%20are%20also%20confronting%20a%20generational%20shift.%20Research%20from%20McKinsey%20suggests%20that%20while%20many%20Gen%20Zers%20express%20interest%20in%20working%20in%20manufacturing%2C%20not%20enough%20of%20them%20are%20taking%20jobs%20at%20factories%20to%20fill%20vacancies%2C%20and%20that%20they're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Fcapabilities%2Foperations%2Four-insights%2Ffrom-hire-to-inspire-getting-and-keeping-gen-z-in-manufacturing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20likely%20than%20older%20workers%20to%20leave%20those%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPepsiCo%20argues%20that%20it%20can't%20continue%20to%20have%20employees%20perform%20most%20tasks%20manually%20while%20cost-effectively%20churning%20out%20enough%20food%20and%20drinks%20to%20meet%20demand.%20So%20it%20trains%20workers%20to%20monitor%20autonomous%20machines%20and%20ensure%20they're%20working%20safely%20and%20efficiently.%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20taking%20an%20analog%20worker%2C%20and%20you%20are%20making%20them%20a%20digital%20worker%2C%26quot%3B%20Kanioura%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20modernization%20efforts%20include%20how%20it%20puts%20together%20variety%20packs%2C%20such%20as%20those%20containing%20several%20small%20bags%20of%20Ruffles%2C%20Doritos%2C%20Cheetos%2C%20and%20Fritos%3A%20While%20workers%20used%20to%20assemble%20the%20packs%2C%20machines%20are%20increasingly%20taking%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20it%20has%20invested%20in%20automation%2C%20PepsiCo's%20total%20workforce%20has%20swelled%3A%20It%20grew%20by%2020%25%2C%20to%20318%2C000%2C%20over%20the%20five%20years%20that%20ended%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2249fb841a-5ce1-4f54-8631-44d495ffdaa5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECreating%20more%20intelligent%20warehouses%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPepsiCo%20says%20it%20considers%20most%20of%20the%20company's%20warehouses%20%26quot%3Bintelligent%26quot%3B%20facilities%20with%20tech%20that%20allows%20employees%20to%20track%20and%20control%20the%20movement%20of%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20uses%20sensors%20and%20AI%20to%20help%20with%20predictive%20maintenance%20checks%20and%20quality-control%20measures%20%E2%80%94%20for%20example%2C%20using%20patterns%20to%20identify%20a%20machine%20or%20vehicle%20that's%20likely%20to%20malfunction%20and%20cause%20problems%20later%20on.%20Rather%20than%20suffering%20a%20shutdown%20when%20a%20motor%20breaks%20on%20the%20tortilla-chip%20line%2C%20PepsiCo%20can%20preemptively%20replace%20the%20motor%20the%20next%20time%20the%20line%20is%20scheduled%20for%20downtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20able%20to%20turn%20that%20data%20into%20action%20is%20important%2C%2