%20one%20end%20to%20keep%20it%20attached%20to%20the%20plastic%20base.%20You%20smooth%20down%20the%20silicone%20over%20the%20filled%20tray%20and%20it%20adheres%20to%20the%20plastic%20so%20that%20no%20water%20escapes%20even%20if%20you%20flip%20the%20tray%20upside%20down%20(which%20we%20did).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plastic%20base%20produced%20crescent%20shaped%20ice%20cubes%20that%20released%20easily%20with%20one%20or%20two%20taps%20on%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20tray.%20If%20you're%20looking%20for%20aesthetically%20pleasing%20ice%2C%20this%20tray%20may%20not%20be%20best%20for%20you%20because%20our%20cubes%20came%20out%20irregularly%20shaped%20(though%20still%20perfectly%20serviceable).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22OXO%20Good%20Grips%20No-Spill%20Ice%20Cube%20Tray%20final%20image.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3f58faab37011780af979%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELily%20Alig%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20it%20isn't%20entirely%20leakproof%2C%20the%20stable%20plastic%20lid%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipgf_072517_best-ice-cube-trays-20%26h%3Dc92264bca2cee921a4d03a6faa5b9bee443bcc4f5d2289dfa4803f23b4d1a35a%26postID%3D61b8efc6f2a36b1ac9f414f3%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fkitchen%252Fbest-ice-cube-tray%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.target.com%252Fp%252Fice-cube-tray-made-by-design-8482%252F-%252FA-79607092%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETarget%20Made%20By%20Design%20Ice%20Cube%20Tray%3C%2Fa%3E%20gives%20you%20the%20best%20stacking%20opportunities%20of%20the%20trays%20we%20tested.%20The%20frame%20and%20lid%20are%20plastic%2C%20but%20the%20bottom%20is%20silicone.%20Instead%20of%20twisting%20and%20cracking%20the%20ice%2C%20you%20can%20push%20on%20the%20silicone%20base%20and%20pop%20out%20the%20cubes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20to%20look%20for%5C%22%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20an%20ice%20cube%20tray%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShape%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20ice%20might%20be%20the%20last%20thing%20on%20your%20mind%20when%20preparing%20a%20cocktail%20or%20a%20glass%20of%20ice%20water%2C%20experts%20told%20us%20that%20choosing%20the%20right%20size%20and%20shape%20cubes%20can%20make%20your%20drink%20taste%20better%20or%20stay%20colder%20longer.%20Joseph%20Gitter%2C%20senior%20editor%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americastestkitchen.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20Test%20Kitchen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20us%20that%20ice%20with%20a%20lower%20surface%20area%20to%20volume%20ratio%20(i.e.%2C%20bigger%20cubes)%20takes%20longer%20to%20melt%2C%20cooling%20drinks%20slowly%20without%20diluting%20them.%20On%20the%20flipside%2C%20small%20cubes%20or%20crushed%20ice%20cool%20drinks%20faster%2C%20but%20provide%20more%20dilution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Most%20of%20the%20best%20ice%20cube%20trays%20are%20now%20made%20out%20of%20silicone%20instead%20of%20plastic.%20The%20flexible%20material%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20remove%20frozen%20cubes%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20have%20jumbo%20or%20spherical%20ice.%20Unfortunately%2C%20silicone%20is%20known%20to%20absorb%20odors%20from%20its%20surroundings.%20A%20trip%20to%20the%20dishwasher%20will%20sort%20this%20out%2C%20but%20if%20you're%20extra%20sensitive%20to%20smells%20and%20tastes%20on%20your%20ice%2C%20try%20a%20traditional%20plastic%20tray.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStorage%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20No%20one%20wants%20valuable%20freezer%20space%20taken%20up%20by%20even%20the%20best%20ice%20cube%20trays.%20Trays%20with%20lids%20or%20plastic%20frames%20are%20easier%20to%20stack%20and%20store%20in%20your%20freezer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20we%20test%5C%22%3EHow%20we%20tested%20ice%20cube%20trays%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20white%20W%26amp%3BP%20Ice%20Tray%20stained%20with%20coffee%20and%20coffee%20ice%20cubes%20next%20to%20it%2C%20showing%20how%20we%20tested%20the%20tray%20for%20scent%20and%20stain%20retention.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6079a0894206150018175e38%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20ice%20cube%20tray%20stained%20with%20coffee%2C%20as%20part%20of%20our%20testing%20for%20odor%20and%20stain%20retention.%3Cp%3ELily%20Alig%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20consulted%20two%20experts%20on%20the%20uses%20of%20different%20ice%20shapes%2C%20how%20to%20make%20clear%20ice%2C%20and%20how%20to%20solve%20common%20ice%20problems.%20We%20spoke%20with%20Joseph%20Gitter%2C%20senior%20editor%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americastestkitchen.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20Test%20Kitchen%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20recipe%20developer%20for%20How%20to%20Cocktail%2C%20and%20Micah%20Melton%2C%20Beverage%20Director%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theaviary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Aviary%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tested%2016%20ice%20cube%20trays%2C%20making%20ice%20between%20three%20and%20five%20times%20in%20each%20tray%20according%20to%20the%20following%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEase%20of%20use%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20ideal%20tray%20is%20easy%20to%20bring%20to%20the%20freezer%20without%20spilling%20water%2C%20releases%20the%20ice%20without%20too%20much%20effort%2C%20and%20can%20be%20stacked%20in%20the%20freezer.%20We%20evaluated%20each%20tray%20based%20on%20these%20qualities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPerformance%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20evaluated%20the%20appearance%20and%20taste%20of%20the%20finished%20ice.%20We%20looked%20for%20sharp-edged%20cubes%20and%20smooth%20spheres.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOdor%20retention%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Silicone%20is%20a%20porous%20material%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20can%20absorb%20scent%20that%20then%20imparts%20a%20taste%20or%20smell%20to%20the%20ice.%C2%A0We%20froze%20coffee%20in%20the%20ice%20cube%20trays%2C%20emptied%20and%20washed%20them%2C%20smelled%20them%2C%20and%20then%20froze%20water%20in%20the%20trays%20to%20see%20if%20the%20coffee%20taste%20or%20smell%20remained.%20(It's%20worth%20noting%20that%20all%20but%20one%20of%20the%20trays%20passed%20this%20test.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaking%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20For%20trays%20with%20sealable%20lids%2C%20we%20flipped%20unfrozen%2C%20full%20trays%20upside%20down%20to%20see%20if%20water%20spilled%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20make%20clear%20ice%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20make%20clear%20ice%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20factors%20that%20make%20ice%20cloudy%3A%20the%20direction%20the%20water%20freezes%20and%20impurities%20or%20air%20bubbles%20in%20the%20water.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20ice%20cube%20trays%20are%20not%20insulated%2C%20so%20water%20freezes%20from%20the%20outside%20in%20and%20from%20all%20directions.%20Safe%20tap%20water%20contains%20impurities%20that%20aren't%20dangerous%20to%20drink%2C%20but%20can%20impact%20the%20flavor%20of%20the%20water%20and%20the%20appearance%20of%20the%20ice.%20As%20water%20freezes%2C%20it%20also%20absorbs%20some%20of%20the%20surrounding%20air.%20The%20absorbed%20air%20bubbles%20and%20the%20impurities%20are%20pushed%20towards%20the%20center%20of%20the%20ice%20as%20the%20outer%20layer%20freezes%20first.%20The%20air%20bubbles%20and%20impurities%20interfere%20with%20forming%20an%20organized%20crystal%20lattice%20and%20so%20the%20ice%20appears%20cloudy%2C%20said%20Gitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20making%20clear%20ice%2C%20you%20eliminate%20or%20limit%20those%20bubbles%20and%20impurities%20and%20focus%20the%20direction%20of%20freezing.%20%26quot%3BEssentially%20the%20process%20involves%20freezing%20the%20ice%20from%20a%20single%20direction%20versus%20all%20directions%20like%20a%20standard%20freezer%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Melton.%20To%20make%20clear%20ice%20at%20home%2C%20first%20purify%20your%20water%20by%20boiling%20it.%20Then%2C%20you%20can%20follow%20Gitter's%20technique%20of%20insulating%20an%20ice%20tray%20by%20surrounding%20it%20with%20dish%20towels%20and%20leaving%20the%20top%20exposed%20so%20it%20only%20freezes%20from%20the%20top%20down.%20We%20detail%20some%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fhow-to-make-clear-ice%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eother%20methods%20of%20making%20clear%20ice%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20aesthetics%2C%20clear%20ice%20is%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20an%20odor%20or%20taste%20because%20it%20doesn't%20contain%20absorbed%20gases%20from%20the%20surrounding%20air%2C%20according%20to%20Melton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FAQs%5C%22%3EFAQs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20large%20ice%20cubes%20next%20to%20each%20other.%20The%20left%20one%20is%20cloudier%20than%20the%20right%20one%2C%20which%20is%20an%20example%20of%20clear%20ice%20made%20from%20a%20TrueCubes%20tray.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F625da881d2039d0019ba3c3f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELily%20Alig%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3EAre%20ice%20cube%20trays%20dishwasher%20safe%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ECleaning%20instructions%20vary%20by%20product%2C%20so%20we%20recommend%20consulting%20the%20manufacturer's%20instructions.%20All%20but%20one%20of%20our%20top%20picks%20is%20dishwasher%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EWhy%20does%20ice%20sometimes%20have%20an%20odor%3F%20How%20can%20you%20deodorize%20an%20ice%20cube%20tray%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWater%20absorbs%20air%20as%20it%20freezes%2C%20which%20can%20impact%20the%20flavor.%20Additionally%2C%20silicone%20is%20a%20porous%20material%20that%20can%20absorb%20scent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20methods%20to%20deal%20with%20this%20problem.%20Tovolo%20recommends%20soaking%20its%20trays%20for%20an%20hour%20in%20a%2050-50%20mixture%20of%20white%20vinegar%20and%20water.%20For%20trays%20made%20wholly%20out%20of%20silicone%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Fwirecutter%2Fblog%2Fhow-to-get-smells-out-of-silicone-kitchenware%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20baking%20the%20trays%20for%2020%20minutes%20at%20250%20degrees%20F%20or%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EWhy%20should%20I%20use%20large%20cubes%20or%20spheres%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20reason%20to%20use%20large%20cubes%20or%20spheres%20is%20to%20chill%20alcoholic%20beverages%20without%20diluting%20them.%20For%20example%2C%20spheres%20have%20a%20lower%20surface%20area%20to%20volume%20ratio%20than%20regular%20ice%20cubes.%20%26quot%3BIce%20spheres%20are%20the%20worst%20at%20making%20a%20drink%20cold%2C%20but%20dilute%20it%20the%20least%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gitter.%20This%20is%20why%20large%20cubes%20are%20most%20ideal%20for%20a%20straight%20spirit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20large%20ice%20cubes%20or%20spheres%20aren't%20perfect%20for%20all%20drinks.%20Some%20cocktails%20are%20meant%20to%20be%20diluted%20and%20slow%20melting%20ice%20can%20change%20the%20intended%20flavor.%20Gitter%20mentioned%20martinis%20as%20an%20example%20of%20this%20because%2C%20traditionally%2C%20the%20gin%20and%20vermouth%20are%20stirred%20with%20regular%20ice%20cubes%20before%20serving.%20The%20stirring%20action%20starts%20the%20melting%20process%2C%20which%20chills%20and%20dilutes%20the%20drink%20to%20a%20palatable%20flavor.%20An%20ice%20sphere%20wouldn't%20melt%20quickly%20enough%20for%20this%20purpose%2C%20and%20you'd%20be%20left%20with%20a%20too%20strong%20and%20too%20warm%20cocktail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20recommend%20using%20large%20cubes%20or%20spheres%20when%20serving%20straight%20spirits%2C%20or%20when%20you%20want%20to%20keep%20a%20drink%20cold%20without%20changing%20its%20flavor%20and%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20overall%3A%20W%26amp%3BP%20Everyday%20Ice%20Cube%20Tray%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20W%26amp%3BP%20Everyday%20Tray%20in%20white%2C%20shown%20with%20the%20ice%20it%20made%20sitting%20between%20the%20tray%20and%20its%20lid.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6079988c74da0300181e2105%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELily%20Alig%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBest%20for%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20All%20types%20of%20beverages%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Silicone%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDishwasher%20safe%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Yes%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBPA-free%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Yes%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPros%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIce%20cubes%20come%20out%20easily%2C%20you%20can%20remove%20exactly%20as%20many%20as%20you%20need%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECons%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20time%20consuming%20to%20empty%20the%20whole%20tray%20of%20ice%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20construction%20of%20the%20Everyday%20Tray%20is%20unique%20among%20the%20ice%20cube%20trays%20I%20tested%2C%20and%20is%20one%20of%20the%20big%20reasons%20why%20this%20is%20the%20best%20ice%20cube%20tray%20I%20tested.%20The%20Everyday%20Tray%20is%20made%20of%20silicone%20and%20none%20of%20the%20cubes%20share%20a%20wall%2C%20so%20you%20can%20release%20them%20one%20at%20a%20time%20by%20applying%20pressure%20to%20the%20bottom.%20I%20also%20found%20that%20this%20helps%20t