host-meghan-mccain-criticizes-republican-vp-candidate-jd-vance-for-childless-cat-ladies-remark%2Famp_articleshow%2F112049460.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fex-tv-show-host-meghan-mccain-criticizes-republican-vp-candidate-jd-vance-for-childless-cat-ladies-remark%2Famp_articleshow%2F112049460.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mamata%20Banerjee%20Can%20Make%20Any%20Comment%20Against%20Governor%20Within%20Laws%3A%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Calcutta%20High%20Court%20on%20Friday%20directed%20that%20Bengal%20Chief%20Minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20is%20free%20to%20make%20any%20statement%20concerning%20Governor%20C%20V%20Ananda%20Bose%2C%20not%20crossing%20the%20contours%20of%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20public%20duty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOtherwise%2C%20the%20appellants%20run%20the%20risk%20of%20being%20exposed%20to%20a%20claim%20for%20heavy%20damages%20and%20other%20retaliatory%20actions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20division%20bench%2C%20comprising%20Justices%20Biswaroop%20Chowdhury%20and%20I%20P%20Mukerji%2C%20said%20modifying%20the%20single%20bench%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Banerjee%20and%20Trinamool%20Congress%20leader%20Kunal%20Ghosh%20had%20moved%20an%20appeal%20before%20a%20division%20bench%2C%20challenging%20an%20interim%20order%20by%20a%20single%20bench%20directing%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20and%20three%20others%20not%20to%20make%20any%20defamatory%20or%20incorrect%20statement%20against%20the%20Governor%20by%20way%20of%20publication%20and%20on%20social%20platforms%20till%20August%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20noted%20that%20the%20lawyers%20for%20the%20respondents%20in%20the%20defamation%20suit%20have%20%26quot%3Bvery%20correctly%20stated%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20statements%20referred%20to%20in%20the%20body%20of%20the%20judgment%20of%20the%20single%20judge%20%26quot%3Bhave%20not%20even%20prima%20facie%20been%20declared%20to%20be%20defamatory%20of%20his%20excellency%20or%20incorrect%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20absence%20of%20such%20declaration%2C%20what%20is%20the%20defamatory%20statement%20referred%20to%20in%20the%20impugned%20order%20which%20is%20being%20restrained%20from%20being%20published%20in%20future%20is%20not%20known.%20This%20order%20applies%20to%20statements%20being%20made%20by%20the%20appellants%20in%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20division%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPassing%20the%20order%2C%20it%20observed%20that%20a%20man's%20reputation%20is%20sacrosanct%20to%20him%20and%20that%20the%20law%20gives%20him%20the%20right%20to%20protect%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20important%20part%20of%20this%20reputation%20is%20his%20moral%20character%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20observed%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20is%20conferred%20on%20every%20citizen%20of%20India%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHolding%20that%20this%20right%20%26quot%3Bcannot%20be%20throttled%20or%20gagged%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20bench%20said%20this%20freedom%20of%20expression%20is%20subject%20to%20reasonable%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20one%20of%20the%20restrictions%20applicable%20in%20this%20case%20is%20the%20restriction%20that%20applies%20to%20words%2C%20spoken%20or%20written%2C%20that%20tend%20to%20defame%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20observed%20that%20public%20has%20the%20right%20to%20know%20the%20truth%20and%20if%20the%20truth%20is%20in%20the%20public%20interest%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20public%20has%20every%20right%20to%20expose%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20this%20right%20is%20vested%20in%20every%20citizen%2C%20such%20right%20is%20vested%20with%20more%20responsibility%20in%20the%20Chief%20Minister%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20also%20said%20that%20expression%20of%20this%20freedom%20is%2C%20however%2C%20subject%20to%20certain%20conditions%20under%20the%20law%20of%20defamation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20is%20that%20it%20should%20stand%20the%20test%20of%20justification%20or%20truth%20or%20must%20be%20a%20fair%20comment%20or%20the%20maker%20of%20the%20statement%20must%20owe%20a%20duty%20to%20the%20persons%20to%20whom%20the%20defamatory%20statement%20was%20published%2C%20which%20is%20described%20as%20qualified%20privilege.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20maker%20fails%20the%20test%20he%20is%20liable%20to%20pay%20damages%20in%20the%20civil%20action%20and%20may%20be%20charged%20with%20commission%20of%20an%20offence%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bose%20had%20sought%20to%20restrain%20Ms%20Banerjee%2C%20two%20newly%20elected%20MLAs%20and%20another%20Trinamool%20Congress%20leader%20from%20issuing%20remarks%20in%20connection%20with%20alleged%20incidents%20at%20Raj%20Bhavan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bengal%20Governor%20filed%20the%20defamation%20suit%20against%20Mamata%20Banerjee's%20comment%20that%20women%20had%20expressed%20fear%20about%20visiting%20the%20Raj%20Bhavan%2C%20which%20he%20said%20were%20%26quot%3Berroneous%20and%20slanderous%20impressions%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Minister%20made%20the%20comment%20while%20expressing%20her%20displeasure%20over%20the%20confusion%20regarding%20the%20oath-taking%20ceremony%20of%20two%20newly%20elected%20party%20MLAs.%20She%20had%20backed%20their%20decision%20of%20not%20accepting%20the%20Governor's%20invitation%20to%20go%20to%20Raj%20Bhavan%20and%20attend%20the%20oath%20ceremony%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MLAs%2C%20Sayantika%20Banerjee%20and%20Reyat%20Hossain%20Sarkar%2C%20had%20written%20to%20him%20seeking%20to%20take%20oath%20at%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722014460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fhjuvb57g_mamata-banerjee_625x300_23_July_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmamata-banerjee-can-make-any-comment-against-governor-withi